  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-10-1701872728499-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-10-1701872728499-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-10-1701872728499-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-10-1701872728499-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-10-1701872728499-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato cubes </strong>and<strong> halved Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give it a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the sweet potato has softened</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-11-1701872735320-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-11-1701872735320-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-11-1701872735320-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-11-1701872735320-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-11-1701872735320-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>cashew nuts</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632225839975-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632225839975-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632225839975-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632225839975-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632225839975-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Tear in <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>coriander</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and blitz – this is your <strong>laksa paste</strong></p><p>Remove <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>laksa paste </strong>(save the rest for later!) and add it to a bowl with the<strong> chopped cashew nuts</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>cashew sambal</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632225861911-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632225861911-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632225861911-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632225861911-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632225861911-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> rice noodles</strong> to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong>, then set aside for 10 min or until softened with a slight bite</p><p>Once softened, drain the <strong>noodles </strong>and set aside then peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based deep pan or pot (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632225868621-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632225868621-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632225868621-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632225868621-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632225868621-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 800ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1.2L]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.6L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>remaining tamari soy sauce </strong>– this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632225898710-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632225898710-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632225898710-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632225898710-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632225898710-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has started to caramelise, add the <strong>laksa paste</strong>,<strong> sriracha</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>red</strong> <strong>Thai curry paste </strong>and cook for 1 min until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and<strong> rice noodles</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 2-5 min or until the noodles are tender – this is your <strong>laksa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632225937898-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632225937898-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632225937898-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632225937898-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632225937898-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>laksa</strong> in bowls and top with the<strong> roasted sweet potato </strong>and<strong> roasted Tenderstem broccoli</strong></p><p>Tear over the <strong>remaining coriander leaves</strong> and dollop over the <strong>spicy cashew</strong> <strong>sambal</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
